http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Coffee-grower-consumes-poison-dies/article14022583.ece

A coffee grower, who attempted suicide by consuming poison on Sunday night, died in a hospital here on Tuesday.The deceased has been identified as K.R. Paramesh (46) of Kanigere village in Alur taluk. His relatives had admitted him to Hassan Institute of Medical Sciences. He is survived by wife, son and daughter Paramesh owned four acres of land on which he cultivated coffee.According to his relatives, he was unhappy with the yield, and owed more than Rs. 5 lakh to his friends and banks. Alur police have registered a case of unnatural death.Farmer Paramesh owned four acres of land in Kanigere villageon which he cultivated coffee